eltexErpsMIB.name: eltexErpsMIB
eltexErpsMIB.description: The MIB module for managing Ethernet Ring Protection Switching.

EltexErpsEnabledState.name: EltexErpsEnabledState
EltexErpsEnabledState.description: Indicates whether the state of object is enabled or disabled.

eltexErpsAdminState.name: eltexErpsAdminState
eltexErpsAdminState.description: This object indicates the ERPS state of the bridge.

eltexErpsLogState.name: eltexErpsLogState
eltexErpsLogState.description: This object indicates the ERPS log state of the bridge.

eltexErpsTrapState.name: eltexErpsTrapState
eltexErpsTrapState.description: This object indicates the ERPS trap state of the bridge.

eltexErpsPendingAction.name: eltexErpsPendingAction
eltexErpsPendingAction.description: The action to be done with the pending configuration. copyPendingActive - to copy the pending erps configuration to the active one. copyActivePending - to copy the active erps configuration to the pending one.

eltexErpsPendingActionVlan.name: eltexErpsPendingActionVlan
eltexErpsPendingActionVlan.description: Variable is associated with eltexErpsPendingAction and determines vlan_tag number in config for action copying/revert on pending config

eltexErpsGetConfigId.name: eltexErpsGetConfigId
eltexErpsGetConfigId.description: Set config id fot snmp get.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSVlanTable.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSVlanTable
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSVlanTable.description: This table contains ERPS ring configuration information.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSVlanEntry.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSVlanEntry
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSVlanEntry.description: A list of ERPS ring configuration information.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSVlanId.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSVlanId
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSVlanId.description: The RAPS VLAN is an index of configuration.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSWestPort.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSWestPort
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSWestPort.description: This is one of the Ethernet ring ports. The value 0 indicates the west port is a virtual channel.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSWestPortState.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSWestPortState
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSWestPortState.description: This is the west port state. It may change sometimes. When the west port is configured on a virtual channel, the west port state is always fowarding.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSEastPort.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSEastPort
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSEastPort.description: This is the other Ethernet ring port. The value 0 indicates the west port is a virtual channel.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSEastPortState.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSEastPortState
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSEastPortState.description: This is the east port state. It may change sometimes. When the east port is configured on a virtual channel, the east port state is always fowarding.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRPLPort.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRPLPort
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRPLPort.description: When the port Enable state is enabled, the RPL port's current port role is defined by the application of the ERPS.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerAdminState.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerAdminState
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerAdminState.description: The administrative value of the RPL owner state. The RPL owner is an Ethernet Ring Node adjacent to the RPL that is responsible for blocking its end of the RPL under normal conditions.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRingMEL.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRingMEL
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRingMEL.description: The ring MEL is the maintenance entity group (MEG) level providing a communication channel for ring automatic protection switching (RAPS) information.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSHoldOffTime.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSHoldOffTime
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSHoldOffTime.description: In order to coordinate timing of protection switches at multiple layers.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSGuardTime.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSGuardTime
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSGuardTime.description: This is used to prevent ring nodes from receiving outdated RAPS messages.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSWTRTime.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSWTRTime
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSWTRTime.description: In the revertive mode of operation, to prevent frequent operation of the protection switch due to an intermittent defect, a failed working transport entity must become stable in a fault-free state.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRingState.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRingState
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRingState.description: This indicates the state of the ring: begin, init, idle, or protection.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRingAdminState.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRingAdminState
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRingAdminState.description: This indicates the administrative state of the ring.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerOperStatus.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerOperStatus
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerOperStatus.description: The current operational value of the RPL owner state. The value 'active' is used to indicate that the RPL owner administrative state is enabled and the device is operated as the active RPL owner. The value 'inactive' is used to indicate that the RPL owner administrative state is enabled, but the device is operated as the inactive RPL owner. The value 'disabled' is used to indicate that the RPL owner administrative state of the device is disabled.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList1to1024
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (1-1024) that belongs to the protection VLANs.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (1025-2048) that belongs to the protection VLANs.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (3073-4094) that belongs to the protection VLANs.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSProtocolVersion.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSProtocolVersion
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSProtocolVersion.description: This object indicates the ERPS protocol compatibility with other versions of ITU-T G.8032.

eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRowStatus.name: eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRowStatus
eltexErpsMgmtRAPSRowStatus.description: This object indicates the RowStatus of this entry.

eltexErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlTable.description: This table contains ERPS sub-ring configuration information.

eltexErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlRAPSVlanId.name: eltexErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlRAPSVlanId

eltexErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlSubRingRAPSVlanI.description: This indicates the ring control VLAN-ID of the sub-ring which connects to another ring.

eltexErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlTCPropagationSta.name: eltexErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlTCPropagationState
eltexErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlTCPropagationSta.description: This indicates the state of sub-ring topology change propagation.

eltexErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlRowStatus.description: This object indicates the RowStatus of this entry.

eltexErpsSFDetectedTrap.description: When the signal fail occurs, a trap will be generated.
